  "name": "Maneuver: Bait and Switch",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you're within 5 feet of a creature on your turn, you can expend one superiority die and switch places with that creature, provided you spend at least 5 feet of movement and the creature is willing and isn't incapacitated. This movement doesn't provoke opportunity attacks.</p>\n<p>Roll the superiority die. Until the start of your next turn, you or the other creature (your choice) gains a bonus to AC equal to the number rolled.</p>\n<p><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813;font-size:13px\">Note: After adding this feature to your character, edit this feature's details and set Resource Consumption to Items Uses: Combat Superiority.</em></p>",
